#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1055
msgid ""
"Payroll commonly uses both CLP and UF (Unidad de Fomento), an inflation-"
"indexed unit calculated daily. Contribution caps and tax brackets can shift "
"with UF — making accuracy and timing critical."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1062
msgid "Part 1: Setting Up a Business Entity in Chile"
msgstr "Parte 1: costituire un'entità legale in Cile"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1064
msgid ""
"Chile has modernized incorporation significantly. The process can be faster "
"than many neighbouring countries, but foreign companies still need careful "
"documentation and local representation."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1070
msgid "1) Choose Your Legal Structure"
msgstr "1) Scegli la tua struttura legale"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1072
#, python-format
msgid ""
"For most international businesses, the SpA (Sociedad por Acciones) is a "
"popular option: limited liability, 100%% foreign ownership possible, and "
"only one shareholder required. It's generally flexible and easier to manage "
"than a traditional S.A."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1079
msgid "2) Register the Company"
msgstr "2) Registra la società"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1081
msgid ""
"You can register through the traditional notary route or via the government "
"portal \"Tu Empresa en un Día\". Incorporation typically requires Articles "
"of Incorporation and notarization. If registering from abroad, companies "
"often grant a legalized Power of Attorney (POA) to a local legal "
"representative in Chile."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1088
msgid "3) Obtain Your Tax ID (RUT) with the SII"
msgstr "3) Ottieni il tuo codice fiscale (RUT) presso il SII"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1090
msgid ""
"After registration, you must register with the Chilean Internal Revenue "
"Service (SII — Servicio de Impuestos Internos) to obtain a RUT (Rol Único "
"Tributario). Without a RUT, you cannot hire employees, open a bank account, "
"or operate normally."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1096
msgid "4) Open a Corporate Bank Account"
msgstr "4) Apri un conto bancario aziendale"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1098
msgid ""
"To pay employees locally and remit taxes, you generally need an in-country "
"corporate bank account. This step may require the physical presence of your "
"local legal representative depending on the bank's requirements."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1104
msgid "5) Secure a Municipal License (Patente Municipal)"
msgstr "5) Ottieni una licenza comunale (Patente Municipal)"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1106
msgid ""
"Before commencing operations, apply for a Patente Municipal (municipal "
"business licence) from the municipality where your legal address is "
"registered."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1112
msgid "Part 2: Navigating Payroll & Employment Laws in Chile"
msgstr "Parte 2: orientarsi tra payroll e diritto del lavoro in Cile"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1114
msgid ""
"Payroll is where complexity accelerates. Many statutory caps and tax "
"brackets are tied to UF — so the calculations must be kept current and "
"consistently applied each pay cycle."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1120
msgid "1) Mandatory Employer Contributions"
msgstr "1) Contributi obbligatori del datore di lavoro"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1122
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Employers typically pay statutory contributions in addition to gross salary "
"(often around 4%%–5%%, depending on factors like industry risk)."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1131
#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1196
msgid "Unemployment Insurance (AFC)"
msgstr "Assicurazione contro la disoccupazione (AFC)"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1133
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Employers contribute 2.4%% for permanent employees (and 3%% for fixed-term "
"contracts)."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1142
msgid "Survivor & Disability Insurance (SIS)"
msgstr "Assicurazione invalidità e superstiti (SIS)"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1144
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Typically around 1.5%% (rates can vary based on applicable rules and "
"providers)."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1153
msgid "Work Accident & Disease Insurance (Mutual)"
msgstr "Assicurazione infortuni sul lavoro e malattie professionali (Mutual)"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1155
#, python-format
msgid ""
"A baseline of 0.93%% plus a risk-based premium up to ~3.4%% depending on "
"your industry."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1163
msgid "2) Employee Deductions (Withholdings)"
msgstr "2) Trattenute del dipendente"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1165
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Employers must withhold and remit the employee's share of social security "
"(often ~17.6%% of gross pay) and monthly income tax."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1174
msgid "Pension Fund (AFP)"
msgstr "Fondo pensione (AFP)"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1176
#, python-format
msgid "10%% paid to the private pension administrator chosen by the employee."
msgstr ""
"Il 10%% viene versato all'amministratore pensionistico privato scelto dal "
"dipendente."

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1185
msgid "Health Insurance (FONASA or ISAPRE)"
msgstr "Assicurazione sanitaria (FONASA o ISAPRE)"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1187
#, python-format
msgid ""
"7%% paid to either the public system (FONASA) or a private insurer (ISAPRE)."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1198
#, python-format
msgid "0.6%% for permanent employees (employee portion)."
msgstr "0,6%% per i dipendenti permanenti (quota dipendente)."

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1207
msgid "Income Tax"
msgstr "Imposta sul reddito"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1209
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Progressive monthly tax from 0%% up to 40%%, determined by UF-linked tax "
"brackets."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1217
msgid "3) Legal Gratification (Profit Sharing)"
msgstr "3) Gratifica legale (partecipazione agli utili)"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1219
#, python-format
msgid ""
"Under the Chilean Labour Code, profitable companies must share 30%% of net "
"income with employees, or commonly choose a guaranteed bonus of 25%% of base "
"salary (capped at 4.75× the minimum wage) paid monthly to satisfy the "
"requirement."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1225
msgid "Part 3: The Danger of Vendor Bloat"
msgstr "Parte 3: il rischio dell'eccesso di fornitori"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1227
msgid ""
"Many companies start with a local accounting firm — but expansion across "
"LATAM can create a fragmented vendor stack: PDFs, spreadsheets, different "
"currencies, and inconsistent definitions. In Chile, small UF-related "
"miscalculations or late filings can trigger immediate and compounding "
"penalties."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1234
msgid "Part 4: How ExactusPay Accelerates Your Expansion"
msgstr "Parte 4: come ExactusPay accelera la tua espansione"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1236
msgid ""
"ExactusPay eliminates friction by replacing fragmented local vendors with a "
"single, technology-driven ecosystem built for the Global South."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1245
msgid "Predictive Payroll Simulations"
msgstr "Simulazioni paghe strategiche"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1246
msgid ""
"Model Total Cost of Employment before you hire. Input base salary and "
"simulate TCOE using the latest UF, caps, and Legal Gratification rules."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1250
msgid "Zero-Error Compliance"
msgstr "Conformità basata sull'IA"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1251
msgid ""
"Automated legal logic keeps calculations current when statutory caps or tax "
"rules change — ensuring filings remain compliant and audit-ready."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1255
msgid "Global-Standardized Reporting"
msgstr "Reportistica standardizzata a livello globale"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1256
msgid ""
"Normalize Chile payroll data into the same reporting format as the UK, "
"Brazil, or Nigeria so CFOs get one unified dashboard."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1260
msgid "24/7 Native Support"
msgstr "Supporto nativo 24/7"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1261
msgid ""
"Round-the-clock support from experts with native fluency in Spanish and "
"Portuguese — acting as an extension of your HR team."
msgstr ""

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1265
msgid "Next step"
msgstr "Prossimi passi"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1267
msgid "Ready to scale without the complexity?"
msgstr "Pronto a scalare senza complessità?"

#: home/templates/articles/cl/article_0001.html:1268
msgid ""
"Geographic borders shouldn't block access to top talent, and local "
"compliance shouldn't slow growth. If you're planning an expansion into Chile "
